<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Yes — the call passes saddr and saddr_size to digest_update without validating that saddr_size does not exceed the actual size of the object pointed to by saddr. If digest_update uses a string.h function such as memcpy/memmove to copy saddr_size bytes, an oversized saddr_size (for example, saddr actually points to a struct sockaddr_in of ~16 bytes but saddr_size is larger) will cause a read beyond the bounds of the saddr object, violating Rule 21.17.
